    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Design which originally appeared in Chippendale's Director for garden tables with a top carved in the form of an open scallop shell; often silver gilt or painted to look like mother of pearl.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
